# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Lat Media Ideation Tool - environment variables
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# For local development you can usually ignore this file. Defaults use ./data
# for SQLite storage and do not require Basic Auth.
#
# Integration API keys (OpenAI, Claude, YouTube, Brave, 69labs) are entered
# INSIDE the running app at /settings/integrations — NOT here. They're stored
# in the local SQLite database, which means they survive restarts and are
# never committed to git.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` only if you want to override one of the settings
# below. `.env` is gitignored.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Override the data folder location. By default the app uses `./data` next
# to package.json — solid default, do not change unless you have a specific
# reason (e.g. you want the DB on an external drive).
# DATA_DIR=/absolute/path/to/data

# Optional fallback for Reddit/Web Signals via Brave Search. You can also
# paste a Brave key in /settings/integrations; the local app setting wins.
# BRAVE_SEARCH_API_KEY=

# Basic Auth gate. Leave blank locally. Only set both if you ever expose the
# app to the internet (e.g. via ngrok / Tailscale Funnel) and want a login
# prompt in front of it.
# APP_USERNAME=
# APP_PASSWORD=
